  "notes": "BASE LIST: The entity roster below is transcribed verbatim from the consolidated Cuba Restricted List published in the Federal Register effective July 14, 2025 (90 FR 31558, Public Notice 12714, FR Doc 2025-13149), which is the most recent FULL machine-readable consolidated CRL. That notice added seven hotels and re-organized the list by province; all other entries were effective February 6, 2025 unless an entry-specific date is noted. The State Department program page (state.gov) is JavaScript/image-rendered and could not be machine-extracted, so the Federal Register raw text was used as the authoritative source. TOTAL ENTITY COUNT: 236 named entities/sub-entities across 11 category groups (provinces consolidated into the 'Hotels' category for the output shape, with province/cayo retained as per-entity metadata; the source breaks hotels out by province/cayo). This sits at the low end of the ~230-250 estimate; every entry is transcribed from the consolidated CRL and no fabricated entries were added. NUMBERING/CAVEATS per the notice: (1) entities owned/controlled by another listed entity are NOT themselves restricted unless separately named; (2) parenthetical activities are illustrative only. also_sdn FLAGS: As of June 2026, EO 14404 (signed May 1, 2026) created a secondary-sanctions program and OFAC/State designated certain CRL entities to the SDN List. Entities on BOTH the CRL and SDN List that are flagged also_sdn=true here: GAESA (SDN since Dec 21, 2020; re-affirmed/designated under EO 14404 May 7, 2026), MININT (SDN May 18, 2026), PNR (SDN May 18, 2026), and MINFAR (SDN June 4, 2026). Other May/June 2026 EO 14404 SDN designations (Moa Nickel S.A., Minera La Victoria S.A., Committees for the Defense of the Revolution/CDR, Cuban Institute of Friendship with the Peoples/ICAP, Amistur Cuba S.A., and several individuals such as Ania Guillermina Lastres Morera and Miguel Diaz-Canel Bermudez) are SDN-only and are NOT on the CRL, so they are intentionally NOT added as CRL entities. GAPS: Could not directly machine-read the live state.gov CRL page to detect any CRL-specific update published after July 14, 2025; no such post-July-2025 CRL update was found in searches as of 2026-06-20, so the July 14, 2025 consolidated list is treated as current.",
